< review>
This is one of my go-to spots! I ALWAYS shop at THIS Dollar General, even when I lived in peach/olive (area). Great staff, products, PRICES. Me N Ed's (our fav pizza spot) is there, there's a bingo place- well "activity center"- THAT'S GREAT! Liquor store, bicycle shop, beauty shop, beauty supply store, tv store & repair shop, motor scooter shop...alot more honestly. It always boggles my mind- WHO goes here? Is it popular? (It should & COULD be!) I dig this center.</review>

< Review>
I enjoy this shopping center for its proximity to my home, the VERY Inexpensive grocery, clothing, household essentials, home goods, toys, OTC Medicines, make-up, shoes, hats, shower essentials, cleaning supplies, garden supplies & much more at The Dollar General. I come usually 2x per week. Also being a smoker- the liquor store has GREAT PRICES on smokes- if your not picky- 4$/pack! That's almost unheard of. Even the Casino cigarettes are about that price and increasing! Also has a beauty parlor, bingo hall, Me-n-Ed's pizzeria, and a few other shops as well. Great little shopping center with discounts to be found! & right across from the U.S Post Officeüòâ</Review>

<rate>4<//rate>< Review>
The shops/stores/restaurants are terrific (Butterfish - yum! - Blaze Pizza, Aqua Nail salon, a bank). The parking lot, though, is DUMB. To get to Five Guys or Butterfish in the northeast corner, you have to cut around the weird L shape of the lot, no matter which way you approach. Bad design.
Lots of room to add to this center - I'm sure it will grow.
Fix the dumb parking design, though.< /Review>

< Review>
Don't be intimidated by its appearance and location. This shopping center is filled with little gems like Hello Boba! You are welcomed by the busy staff, through Covid-compliant glass, wearing masks. We ordered Jasmine green tea, Royal milk tea, and the sea foam black tea. All with brown sugar boba, without extra charge. We were able to adjust the sweetness to our liking. They were allmade well, we finished them before getting back on the freeway. The boba was soft and chewy, the way they're meant to be.</Review>

< text>
I really enjoyed the Boba milk teas I ordered from here.

They are also offering Happy Hour prices during the week from Mon-Fri, 4pm-7pm (BOGO on Boba Milk Tea or Thai Milk Tea). They offer reg size (small) or bigger for $.50 more. Can't beat the HH deal, though.

I would've appreciated if they offered non-dairy milk alternatives for ALL of their drinks instead of just certain ones. Apparently, the mixes are already made so they cannot substitute/customize according to your needs.<//text>

< Text>
Newly opened Hello Boba that offers coffee, bubble tea and desserts. They are located in a small plaza by Peck rd and Garvey avenue. They have a wide variety of milk and fruit tea boba. Interior atmosphere was welcoming and  relaxing. Inside was clean, organized and spacious. Its interior decor was simple albeit cute. Some of their milk tea boba and smoothies were pretty standard however what captivated me was their fruity selection called mojito (original, mint leaves, lime, mango, peach, watermelon). I ordered a large mojito with boba and it was really good. It is something other boba shops in SGV don‚Äôt have. It‚Äôs refreshing, perfectly sweetened and divine. The concatenated boba pearl was chewy, warm and soft just the way I like it. Prices were inexpensive and very competitive. They have regular and large size containers. Furthermore, it has positive and motivating message at the back of every containers. Staff was nice and assiduous. Overall I HIGHLY recommend Hello Boba and will definitely try their other boba.< /Text>

<Date>1620675039169< /Date><Rate>1<//Rate>< Text>
It really helps when an employee actually knows a store policy.  Sign on the door "Only two parties allowed in the store at one time".  We look in the store, one party of two people, we make the second party and walk in (we are not within 15 feet of anyone in the store and are wearing our masks)... lady behind the counter, You have to wait outside.  Ok, questioning the sign...  "Your sign says two parties, not two people."  Atempting to get a legitimate clarification.  Rudely, she responds...  "You have to wait outside, that is our store policy, if you do not like it, we do not need your business."   She was right, they did not need my business and we went to Doc Bernsteins (one block away).  I do not care if your policy is Two people in the store at one time, if that is what you want, that is fine...  but your sign should say that, not " Two parties", which many people will take to interpret as two groups of people together.  Simple fix, update your store sign to say "Two People".<//Text>

<user_id>111557884895470941076</user_id><name>Paul Malarik Jr< /name><Date>1600937404174<//Date><rate>5< /rate>< Review>
Local review by a local:  Excellent locally made ice-cream that has great creative flavors.  They are doing a great job of being COVID-19 safe, and you order via a window in the door.  The only downsides are samples are not available so you could be stuck with something too sweet for example.  Since I am older, I tend to go with robust flavors with things like pie crust in them.  While I thought the Boysenberry was totally amazing in flavor and reminded me of the long defunct Ben & Jerry's version for decades ago, I could do without pie pieces. In keeping with simplicity, I also had a scoop of Vanilla Bean.  It was refreshing.  While they did have a single flavored Strawberry & a Complex Chocolate, I kind of missed a Coffee or a Pistachio.  There was an intriguing Lemon combo, but without sampling why risk it.  While I see the appeal for the Millennial crowd, us mature folk do enjoy the classics, so please make more of those.  IN any case, it made an excellent dessert after a big meal at Ox & Anchor around the block.  This local ice-cream was also available at the Avila Barn, where sundaes where available.  I am not sure if that is possible in the future here....I guess it depends upon this new C-19 age.  Regardless of the above, it is simply marvelous to see this wonderful venture surviving in downtown SLO, despite the many challenges. Thank you so much for all your hard work!<//Review>

< Text>
Adding into the mix of ice cream places in SLO is McConnell's, a fine sweet delicacy from Santa Barbara. I was very surprised to see one here, but also very relieved that I don't have to drive all the way to Santa Barbara anymore. It kind of appeared out of thin air, but also just in time for finals week at Cal Poly. As ice cream prices go, it is $5.25 for two scoops (called a single scoop) and there are so many options! My favorite thing about them though are the dairy free flavors. Not many people go through the effort to make dairy free flavors and just resort to sorbets which is just sad. Overall, a great place to grab a snack or dessert after a meal!</Text>

<Review>In September 2020 I asked Dr. David Han to redo the bondings he did for me on my upper front teeth in 2010, this visit was 2 weeks before my 66 birthday.
I asked Dr. Han if he would redo the bondings for me because they had worn down a bit and I wanted to lighten them also. I mentioned to him that my upper lip was not as full as it once was and cosmetic surgery was not an option for me.
Dr. Han told me that he could improve the appearance of my front teeth and create an attractive smile by improving the shape, color, also provide a  functional bite, with the bonus of giving me the appearance of a fuller upper lip. Dr. Han and his team took impressions for bleaching trays and for him to make a diagnostic wax-up to show me what my teeth would look like with 6 upper porcelain veneers. I said, with excitement, let's do it!
In November after completing bleaching I went in for my appointment for impressions for the veneers and went home with acrylic temporary veneers.
I truly appreciate how meticulous Dr. Han was from beginning to the end of the process. He worked side by side with his lab to make sure my veneers were exactly what he wanted.
A week later I went in to see him because I managed to dislodge a portion of my temporary. Dr. Han removed my temporary and tried in 2 veneers which led him to make a slight change to achieve the results he was looking for.
December 16th I received my 6 veneers. Dr. Han is truly an artist.Teeth have to be harmonious with the facial shape. Dr.Han achieved that with my veneers, they were so precisely made for me.
Dr. David Han and his team strive for excellence. I'm very grateful for the esthetic and functional results he provided for me. I have beautiful porcelain veneers that have given me a smile that I'm confidant and happy with. Additionally, the veneers created by Dr. Han have given me the appearance of having a fuller upper lip without cosmetic surgery.

Sincerely thank you Dr. Han,
and VIP dental team.

< Text>
Dr. Han is simply amazing.

Thoughtful, caring, thorough and extremely attentive.

When I first looked at getting veneers I was told that I needed jaw surgery. They would need to cut open my jawline and insert a titanium plate to give me my desired smile.

The surgery was going to require 12 months of braces, 6 months of recovery and another 6 months of braces to give me the smile I wanted!

I met one of Dr. Hans clients who had a beautiful simile and she said I absolutely must meet him so I set an appointment for a routine cleaning and consultation.

Dr. Han was the first Dentist that offered me hope for a great smile without surgery!

In fact in the first visit he went above and beyond and created a temporary extension of my front teeth showing me what would be possible without surgery!!

Dr. Han is meticulous and detailed and has had me come back a few times to try the temporaries before finalizing the permanent teeth. I lost a temporary at one point and he got me in the same day without a problem.

He explained the process, the timeline, and the cost and was very detailed in answering all my questions.

Not to mention his staff is incredible - Alex and Daisy are very sweet and have tremendous attention to detail.

I am very happy with the result, the office and the care that he and his team provide.

I highly encourage anyone that is considering a Dentist or cosmetic work to set up a consultation with Dr. Han!< /Text>

< Text>
Dr. Han is the best I was in need of major dental work including bone graphs as well as raising my sinuses to allow the implants to be installed. I went to at least 6 dentists over the past 10 years and they told me that it could not be done. I was going to lose my teeth do to bone loss from an accident I was in and dentures would be the only option that can be done. Dr. Han took x-rays and did an evaluation and said he could do it. He explained the entire procedure that I would have to go thru and that it would take some time to finish the reconstruction of my jaw line and get me basically a new smile and return to having back teeth. Well it was allot of work and it took over a year for healing and getting every thing done in steps which is exactly what he told me. Today I could not be any happier I have my smile back and a full mouth of teeth again everything was done so professionally and with very little pain or down time. This is my experience with Dr. Han after getting 4 veneers on my front teeth.

I went to Dr. Han looking to get the gap in front teeth closed. I came in for bonding because I felt that was the cheapest option that I saw online. Dr. Han went over all the options for me accessing the pros and cons of each. We went over braces, bonding, and veneers. For bonding he even placed some temporary ones on to see how I would look. I decided to go with the veneers because they would look the best and they could last more than 20 years if I take care of them. Dr Han gave his recommendations and the cost and let me think about it and talk with my family to ask their opinion.

My next visit Dr. Han took pictures and made a mold of my mouth and to make a 3D model. With the model he sculpted my teeth the way he wanted to, so I could see what the adjustments would look like before they were permanent. It was a very thorough process. He also took another mold so I can bleach me teeth for a couple weeks to match the lighter color of the veneers.

My next visit Dr. Han showed me the 3D model and went over what looks best for my teeth considering my smile, my face, the size of my lips etc. Then he placed some temporary veneers on, so I can see if I liked them but also Dr. Han wanted me to show my family and ask for their opinion on it. He even called me after a few days to see how it was going and asked for any feedback or if adjustments needed to be made.

My next appointment my veneers went in and Dr. Han placed 4 veneers on my front teeth. I was done in less than two hours and I couldn‚Äôt be any happier. My temporary veneers looked good, but my final ones looked even better! The entire staff was friendly and professional, and I recommend Dr. Han for any dental work.< /review>

< text>
There are not enough words to express my gratitude and satisfaction for VIP Dentistry. I received amazing service from the beginning to the end of my services. The entire staff made me feel welcomed and cared for immensely. They were personable and expressed genuine concern for my problems.

I originally called to make an appointment for my throbbing TMJ discomfort. I was extremely uncomfortable, and they were happy to take me in that day. I did not wait at all, and was seen right away. Not only that, but the staff really took the time to get to know me and make me feel right at home. I am not exaggerating when I say that I was smiling the entire visit.

Normally, dentists and dental offices give me extreme anxiety. However, this office was different from all previous experiences. I felt at home, and extremely comfortable (which I have never felt at any office before!) When Dr. Han came in for my visit, he was extremely personable and kind. I felt like he spent the time to educate me about my condition, provided me all the options, but made me feel listened to and cared for. He was an extraordinary dentist, but he also expressed immense passion for his patients and the improvement of the dental industry in general. It was obvious that he wanted to offer only excellent care, and I certainly did not receive anything less than that.

What touched me most of all was my experience with the office manager. I told her in a prior conversation that I had only been in the area for 1 month for school, and all my family and friends were in San Francisco. While I was waiting for the doctor, she surprisingly came in and simply talked to me and got to know me. She actually brought tears to my eyes due to her genuine empathy and concern. She knew how hard it would be for me to go through these big changes without my support system, so she just wanted to be there for me during the visit. I never experienced that in a dental office, or in life. In this office, I felt cared for not only as a patient, but as a human being. That experience, to me, is priceless in itself.<//text>

I highly recommend Dr. Han for anyone who is looking for the Best care for your teeth.

< Review>
Really good, no frills, no BS burrito place. Whether going in store or drive thru, orders are served up pretty quick. Parking is a bit tight, the neighboring shopping center threatens to tow you away if you park there. There's quite a variety of burritos, including breakfast burros. A small salsa bar adds a spicy touch. Couldn't post a picture because I demolished my California burrito before writing this review.</Review>

<Date>1364622357632< /Date>< Text>
Last time I ever come here for a smog test...

Obviously, I came here to get my biannual smog check.  I had a feeling it wasn't going to pass the inspection part of the smog test due to my after market exhaust.  And... I was right.

The reason I would never come back to these guys is because they only want your money. In the beginning of my smog check, the smog tech checked under my car to inspect the parts to make sure they were all legal.  I noticed him checking it for a good 5-10 min, kept looking at me, then went ahead and proceeded with the smog check. He ran all the tests, backed my car out and then told me the news...

He told me that it didn't pass because of my exhaust and that I would have to get it fixed before it would actually pass. I am livid because he knew well before he performed the test that it would fail because of this.  With that, they just want your money any way they can and don't give a lick about customer service.  I definitely will not be ever coming back here again.< /Text>

<Resp>None</Resp><pics>None< /pics><UserId.>103580795622093245217</UserId.><review>This review specifically goes out to Anthony in the Custom Framing department.

I was tasked by the firm I work for to get my diplomas framed. A coworker recommended Hobby Lobby, so naturally that was my first stop (went to the one across the way from this Michaels location). HORRIBLE experience at Hobby Lobby. I was observing the frame options at hobby lobby when the man working the framing department came out and sarcastically said, if you were ready you should have rung the bell. He asked what I was looking for, and I explained that I was wanting to get my diplomas framed. He was quick to dismiss any of my inquiries into custom framing and instead was pushing me to buy the 50% off ready made frames‚Äîum, if I wanted ready made frames, I would have started there... He seriously would not let it go, and kept insisting I look at the frames already on the floor and go with those. To say I was put off was an understatement. He asked if I had gotten my bachelor's degree. It wasn't until I told him I was looking to frame my Masters AND Law degree that he took me seriously and said, "oh SH**, okay, well if you really want you can do the custom framing..." It was a horrible experience and I decided to take my business elsewhere.

When I got to Michaels‚Äîa COMPLETE 180 from how I was treated in Hobby Lobby. There was no questioning of why I'd want to get custom framing over ready made frames or even of whether I could afford the service. Anthony was so ready and eager to help and exemplified incredible patience. He made great recommendations, walked me through the process and talked me through color options. I also observed how he was working with the customer just previous to us, and saw how he was incredibly professional and understanding to all of us who were waiting at the Framing department. It took me a good 20 minutes to make a decision on my framing options, but Anthony seemed to really understand what an important decision this was‚Äîthe diplomas are more than a piece of paper; they represent years of sacrifice and hard work.

I will definitely be recommending this Michaels and specifically the framing department to any of my friends who are looking to get their diplomas framed. Honestly, give Anthony a raise because he is most deserving.< /review>< username>

<Response>None<//Response>< Pictures>
None</Pictures>
<Text>It's a nice enough Michaels if you like Michaels.  Michaels plays a lot of games with its pricing and coupons, which works for people who like that kind of thing, clipping coupons, paper or digital, going back multiple times, or getting in line mutiple times, to get the coupon discounts on more than one item. But it's a pain for someone who just wants to buy art or craft supplies for a good price. They inflate the original price, then put the item on "sale" so their coupons don't work on it. If they know their price, why not just charge it instead of all the pricing/coupon manipulation. To be a successful Michaels shoppper and get the best prices, you really have to master their sale/coupon/pricing scheme. Never shop at Michaels without going on line first to get the coupons of the day.  Good luck!< /Text></record>

< Review>
For the most part I like this store and find its staff to be very friendly and helpful. Around Christmas time when they have so much seasonal merchandise they can be less able to direct you to what you are looking for, but the other 10 months of the year, they're very able. Since it's a smaller store, I find it better when I know what I need, because I can get in and out quickly. Their selection of products is good, and I rarely need to go elsewhere for most small projects.</Review>

< review>
I've gone in this store 2 times in the last week the first time that I was in I was looking at some framing the framing is advertised 70% off so I went through the whole thing that took like an hour and a half and I got a price quote for my three pictures to be framed and my total came out to be around $130 each I'm told that that's 70% off so that kind of leaves me to wonder who's paying that much to have one picture framed at Michaels. When I asked the gentleman working there he said it's not really exactly like it's 70% off because it's 70% off of the manufacturer's price which is not what they actually sell them for so while it says its 70% off it's not exactly 70% off. I had some things that I had wanted to purchase from walking around the store while I was waiting for the frame price quote so I go to purchase them and I'm standing in a line of about maybe six or seven people there's one person only on the cashier so we're waiting waiting waiting we were in line for about 15 minutes and at this point I had been in the store for over 2 hours with a three-year-old which doesn't really work out very well so I had to abandon the things I wanted to purchase and leave. I went back into the store today and unfortunately only we found some of the things that I wanted to purchase I'm using the time while my son is at school to go to Michaels since I was already expecting a long line and that's exactly what I found the line that I had to wait in for quite some time in order to pay. Long story short Michaels has cute things I want to buy them but I can't go there with my child because when things takes so long when you thought you could just run in and grab a quick decoration and pay you're going to be in line for quite a while waiting it seems. Maybe I caught them on a bad week maybe that's how it always is I'm not sure and I probably won't find out.</review>
